&lt;h2&gt;Cybersecurity for the public good&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At nuHarbor, we help organizations navigate an increasingly complex cybersecurity landscape with confidence. By combining expert guidance, innovative technology, and trusted partnerships, we make security stronger, more effective, and easier to understand. We&#39;re looking for talented individuals who are passionate about solving meaningful challenges, helping clients succeed, and continuously improving alongside a team that values curiosity, collaboration, and impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Why nuHarbor?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At nuHarbor, you&#39;ll find more than a job—you&#39;ll find a team committed to solving meaningful problems, delivering exceptional outcomes, and supporting one another&#39;s growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re always looking for exceptional people who share our passion for cybersecurity, problem-solving, and client success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether your expertise is in security operations, engineering, threat and detection, consulting, compliance, sales and marketing, or another area that supports our mission, we encourage you to introduce yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining our talent community, you&#39;ll help us learn more about your experience, interests, and career goals. As new opportunities become available, our recruiting team may reach out to discuss potential roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The most successful people at nuHarbor tend to have a few things in common:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to helping clients succeed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A desire to continuously learn and improve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity, initiative, and a willingness to solve difficult problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and collaboration skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team-first mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrity, accountability, and professionalism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most importantly, we’re looking for people who align with our core values:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help Clients Win&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Always Improve&lt;br&gt;Protect the House&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Tell Us About Yourself&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re excited about nuHarbor&#39;s mission and interested in future opportunities, we&#39;d love to learn more about you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please submit your application, resume, and areas of interest. Our team will review your information and keep it on file for future opportunities that align with your background and career goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AAP/EEO Statement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Equal Employment Opportunity Policy of NuHarbor Security is to provide a fair and equal employment opportunity for all associates and job applicants regardless of race, color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status or disability. NuHarbor Security hires and promotes individuals solely based on their qualifications for the job to be filled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NuHarbor Security believes that employees should be provided with a working environment which enables each associate to be productive and to work to the best of his or her ability. We do not condone or tolerate an atmosphere of intimidation or harassment based on race, color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, or disability.&amp;nbsp; We expect and require the cooperation of all employees in maintaining a discrimination and harassment-free atmosphere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Cybersecurity for the public good&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At nuHarbor, we help organizations navigate an increasingly complex cybersecurity landscape with confidence. By combining expert guidance, innovative technology, and trusted partnerships, we make security stronger, more effective, and easier to understand. We&#39;re looking for talented individuals who are passionate about solving meaningful challenges, helping clients succeed, and continuously improving alongside a team that values curiosity, collaboration, and impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a SOC Team Lead, you&#39;ll help shape the daily operations and technical excellence of our Security Operations Center. You&#39;ll lead a team of analysts, guide complex investigations, develop operational improvements, and serve as a trusted resource for both clients and teammates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role blends technical leadership, people development, and operational execution. You&#39;ll drive quality, mentor analysts, and help evolve the services that protect our clients every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead by example while embodying nuHarbor&#39;s core values: &lt;strong&gt;Help Clients Win, Always Improve, and Protect the House&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the day-to-day operations of a team of Security Analysts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary escalation point for complex security investigations and incidents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide incident response activities and ensure timely, high-quality client communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review analyst work for quality, consistency, and adherence to operational standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and mentor analysts through technical development and career growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular one-on-one meetings and provide ongoing performance feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform advanced alert triage, investigation, threat hunting, and incident analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve detection quality, analyst efficiency, and client outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain operational documentation, playbooks, and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the evolution of NuHarbor&#39;s detection engineering and automation strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with leadership on escalations, emerging threats, and operational priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with clients while providing meaningful security recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Your Foundation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who brings these minimum qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in a technology-related field and 5+ years of Information Technology experience &lt;strong&gt;OR&lt;/strong&gt; relevant industry certifications and equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting or leading security operations teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience investigating and responding to cybersecurity incidents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with SIEM and EDR technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with alert triage, threat hunting, and incident escalation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing procedures, playbooks, or operational documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and the ability to explain technical concepts clearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience presenting findings and recommendations to stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Authorization to work in the United States&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Stand out With&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may stand out if you have experience with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CrowdStrike&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Splunk Enterprise Security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SOAR platforms and security automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detection engineering and content tuning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scripting and automation

